            <div id="dsq-comment-message-10483" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Richard, I note for the record that you have once again failed to make a moral (or even economic) argument about why capital should be taxed at a lower rate than labor.</p>
<p>Some people (the rich) have capital to offer. Others (the poor) have labor to offer. Why should one be favored over the other? </p>
<p>Aren&#8217;t we supposed to be an egalitarian society?</p>
